@startuml
title Séquence métier — Relancer les virements (admin)
' ------------------------------------------------------------------
' Style impression A4 (PFE FSEG) — lisibilité : polices ~11–12 pt visibles,
' DPI 240, retour à la ligne des messages. Inclure juste après la ligne title.
' Export PNG pour Word/LaTeX : viser largeur <= zone utile A4 (~17 cm).
' ------------------------------------------------------------------
scale max 1550 width
skinparam dpi 240
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam HyperlinkUnderline false

skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam titleFontSize 16
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam arrowThickness 1.25
skinparam wrapWidth 220
skinparam NoteFontSize 10
skinparam LegendFontSize 10
skinparam footerFontSize 10
skinparam headerFontSize 10

skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam ParticipantPadding 14
skinparam BoxPadding 8
skinparam LifeLineBorderColor #444444
skinparam LifeLineBackgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ArrowColor #222222
skinparam ActorBorderColor #222222
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #EEF6FF
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #333333
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF

skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #F8F8F8
skinparam EntityBackgroundColor #F8FFF8
skinparam ControlBackgroundColor #FFF8F0
skinparam BoundaryBackgroundColor #F5F5FF
actor Admin as admin
boundary "Administration (ops)" as UI
control "Contrôleur" as Svc
entity "Base de données" as DB
queue "BullMQ : send-email" as Queue

admin -> UI: Consulter les payouts en echec (evenements)
UI -> Svc: GET /api/admin/ops/failed-payouts?resolved=false&limit=...
Svc -> DB: FailedPayoutEvent.find({ resolved: false }) ...
DB --> Svc: failedPayouts[]
Svc --> UI: 200 { failedPayouts }
UI --> admin: Affichage

admin -> UI: Relancer le traitement (lot)
UI -> Svc: POST /api/admin/ops/retry-payouts { limit? }
note right of Svc
  **Code :** `adminOpsService.retryPayoutsOnce` -> `cronService.retryFailedPayouts`.
  Pour chaque FailedPayoutEvent : si Payout.status == FAILED, repasse le payout en READY
  et incremente retryCount sur l'event (demo / reconciliation interne).
  Pas d'appel HTTP direct a une banque dans cette version.
end note

Svc -> DB: Charger FailedPayoutEvent non resolus (limite)
DB --> Svc: events

loop pour chaque event
  Svc -> DB: Charger Payout par payoutId
  DB --> Svc: payout
  alt payout.status == FAILED
    Svc -> DB: Payout.status = READY, failureReason vide, save
    Svc -> DB: FailedPayoutEvent.retryCount++
  else autre etat
    Svc -> DB: Event resolu ou ignore (selon logique)
  end
end

Svc --> UI: 200 { ok: true, summary }
UI --> admin: Resume

@enduml
